entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: A software project or platform that is experiencing developments in token migration, technical improvements such as streaming functionality and plugin memory architecture, and business model planning. It has a related token AI16Z that is migrating to an ElizaOS token.

entities.name: AI16Z
entities.description: A cryptocurrency token that is undergoing a migration to the ElizaOS token with a 6:1 conversion ratio. Trading of this token has been paused by Kraken.

entities.name: Kraken
entities.description: A cryptocurrency exchange that has announced pausing trading for AI16Z while evaluating support for its migration to ElizaOS tokens. This action creates uncertainty for users holding the token on their platform.

entities.name: Deepseek
entities.description: A provider that can be used through the openrouter plugin for ElizaOS implementation. It is relevant in technical discussions concerning agent connection issues.

entities.name: Openrouter
entities.description: A plugin that allows users to utilize providers such as Deepseek for ElizaOS implementation. It is part of the technical discussions and troubleshooting of agent connection issues.

entities.name: X
entities.description: A social media platform whose API integration costs are a concern for building AI agents on the ElizaOS platform. The high monthly cost is a barrier for developers.

entities.name: ElizaCloud
entities.description: A component or associated platform of ElizaOS with a potential business model involving a marketplace. It aims to provide a platform for developers with revenue sharing and standardized structures.

entities.name: Salesforce AppExchange
entities.description: A marketplace for enterprise applications that serves as a model for ElizaCloud's potential business model. It involves a platform revenue cut for developers.

entities.name: Apple App Store
entities.description: A digital distribution platform for mobile applications that is cited as a model for ElizaCloud's potential marketplace business strategy. It includes revenue sharing with third-party developers.

entities.name: JWK Provider
entities.description: A type of authentication provider being integrated into ElizaOS. Support for JWK providers is part of the authentication improvements and preparation for enterprise deployments.

entities.name: Claude
entities.description: A project or service whose functionality, specifically its 'skills', is being emulated or considered for the plugin memory architecture improvements in ElizaOS. The goal is to tailor the architecture to specific tasks.

entities.name: Odilitime
entities.description: A community member or developer who has provided detailed explanations and suggestions within the ElizaOS community. They have answered questions about token migration and proposed technical solutions.

entities.name: Borko
entities.description: An individual involved in discussions about implementing streaming functionality within the ElizaOS framework. A suggestion for the implementation approach was made to them.

entities.name: Privy
entities.description: A service or platform being integrated into the ElizaOS authentication system. This integration is part of the development of per-user authentication validation on the server.

entities.name: GitHub
entities.description: A web-based platform that hosts software development version control using Git. The elizaOS/eliza repository is hosted here, and its activity, issues, and contributors are tracked.

entities.name: ElizaCloud Marketplace
entities.description: A proposed marketplace for ElizaOS, intended to function similarly to platforms like Salesforce AppExchange or Apple App Store. It focuses on revenue sharing with third-party developers.

entities.name: Babylon
entities.description: An upcoming feature or project related to ElizaOS that contributes to community optimism about the platform's future. Specific details about its function are not provided.
